This directory vendors a third-party PyTorch + Hugging Face implementation of
mHC (Manifold-Constrained Hyper-Connections) used as a baseline by Phase mHC of
Mneme.

Upstream
--------
- Repository: https://github.com/MarcoDotIO/mhc-deepseek-implementation
- License:    MIT (see LICENSE in this directory)
- Vendored from upstream main branch; minor modifications described below.

Paper
-----
DeepSeek, "Manifold-Constrained Hyper-Connections" (mHC).
arXiv:2512.24880 (v1 2025-12-31; v2 2026-01-05).
https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.24880
DOI: 10.48550/arXiv.2512.24880

Modifications versus upstream
-----------------------------
1. Top-level package import path rewritten from ``mhc`` to
   ``deltamemory.baselines.mhc_gpt2`` so it loads as a private Mneme
   baseline without polluting the global ``mhc`` namespace.
   Specifically, in ``transformers/gpt2_mhc.py`` the lines
       from mhc.mhc import MhcProjector
       from mhc.stream_ops import mhc_update, stream_weighted_sum
   were changed to
       from deltamemory.baselines.mhc_gpt2.mhc import MhcProjector
       from deltamemory.baselines.mhc_gpt2.stream_ops import (
           mhc_update, stream_weighted_sum,
       )
2. No algorithmic changes. Sinkhorn-Knopp projection, MhcProjector, mHC
   GPT-2 model code, and the GPT-2 → mHC logits-equivalent conversion remain
   bit-for-bit identical to upstream as of vendoring date.

Why vendor (not pip install)
----------------------------
- Mneme red lines require sha-pinned, audit-ready code paths. Vendoring
  preserves the exact mHC implementation against upstream churn.
- Phase mHC preregistration (``docs/preregistration/mHC_alpha_safe_v1.md``)
  binds H1–H6 to specific arithmetic; we cannot let an upstream patch silently
  shift the numerical behaviour of the third arm.
